\chapter{Tutorial Model}
\label{tutorial-model}

The model layer answers two questions.  First, what information do we
need to describe a tutorial step?  Second, what information do we need
to preserve after the student has interacted with the shell?

We keep the answer deliberately small.  A step has human-facing text,
may optionally open a file in an editor, and carries one or two
machine-checkable expectations; a run stores the recorded text that was
produced while the student worked through the tutorial.


